WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:10.344 --> 00:00:14.639
The desire to go further
has been a part of the American dream

2
00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:17.141
since the founding of our great nation.

3
00:00:17.142 --> 00:00:21.312
We saw the impossible.
and we made it possible.

4
00:00:22.439 --> 00:00:27.193
But there are those few among us
who would try to pull us backwards.

5
00:00:27.194 --> 00:00:29.195
They underestimated us.

6
00:00:29.196 --> 00:00:32.740
- our resilience. our resolve...
<i>- Five. four.</i>

7
00:00:32.741 --> 00:00:35.952
- <i>three. two. one.</i>
- And our desire to look up at the heavens

8
00:00:35.953 --> 00:00:37.496
<i>and never look back.</i>

9
00:00:38.497 --> 00:00:40.248
<i>After one of the most sensational</i>

10
00:00:40.249 --> 00:00:42.375
<i>come-from-behind victories
by a presidential candidate...</i>

11
00:00:42.376 --> 00:00:44.210
<i>called the Mars Seven Alliance.</i>

12
00:00:44.211 --> 00:00:47.088
<i>The agreement aims to end the competition
and distrust that has...</i>

13
00:00:47.089 --> 00:00:49.298
<i>Helios loses its antitrust lawsuit</i>

14
00:00:49.299 --> 00:00:51.717
<i>brought by Exxon. Shell and Halliburton.</i>

15
00:00:51.718 --> 00:00:53.636
- <i>The companies claim...</i>
- Show me the money!

16
00:00:53.637 --> 00:00:56.973
<i>President Wilson
was sworn in. beginning her second term.</i>

17
00:00:56.974 --> 00:00:59.642
<i>The Republican president is the first
openly gay person to hold the office.</i>

18
00:00:59.643 --> 00:01:01.352
<i>Helios CEO. Richard Hilliard.</i>

19
00:01:01.353 --> 00:01:05.231
<i>called their plasma propulsion technology
a "game changer"</i>

20
00:01:05.232 --> 00:01:09.652
<i>because missions will no longer have to
wait for the so-called Mars window...</i>

21
00:01:09.653 --> 00:01:12.280
<i>Survivors of the mission
have safely made it back to Earth.</i>

22
00:01:12.281 --> 00:01:13.698
<i>Stranded on Mars for over a year...</i>

23
00:01:13.699 --> 00:01:15.491
<i>Jung-Gil. first man on Mars.</i>

24
00:01:15.492 --> 00:01:17.451
<i>greeted crowds celebrating his return.</i>

25
00:01:17.452 --> 00:01:20.496
<i>Lee spent months alone on Mars
after his capsule crash-landed...</i>

26
00:01:20.497 --> 00:01:21.998
<i>Your lunar suite awaits.</i>

27
00:01:21.999 --> 00:01:25.334
<i>The first hotel has opened on the moon.
available to the general public...</i>

28
00:01:25.335 --> 00:01:27.670
<i>James Stevens
testified against the defendants.</i>

29
00:01:27.671 --> 00:01:30.673
<i>Stevens struck a plea bargain agreement
with prosecutors last year.</i>

30
00:01:30.674 --> 00:01:32.466
<i>The ABC comedy</i> Ellen <i>has been renewed...</i>

31
00:01:34.052 --> 00:01:37.013
<i>Today. President Wilson
signed the Marriage Inclusion Act.</i>

32
00:01:37.014 --> 00:01:38.682
<i>legalizing same-sex marriage...</i>

33
00:01:39.725 --> 00:01:42.310
The Race to Mars
<i>had its premiere tonight</i>

34
00:01:42.311 --> 00:01:45.271
<i>starring Clint Eastwood as Ed Baldwin.
Jada Pinkett as Danielle Poole...</i>

35
00:01:45.272 --> 00:01:47.690
<i>New breakthroughs in fabrication on Mars</i>

36
00:01:47.691 --> 00:01:50.359
<i>will enable Happy Valley Base
to manufacture aluminum</i>

37
00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:52.278
<i>from materials found
on the Martian surface.</i>

38
00:01:52.279 --> 00:01:54.280
<i>Dubbed
"the successor to the Concorde."</i>

39
00:01:54.281 --> 00:01:57.742
<i>the aircraft is capable of reaching low
Earth orbit and shortening travel time...</i>

40
00:01:57.743 --> 00:02:00.661
<i>Director Stanley Kubrick
died today in England at the age of 70.</i>

41
00:02:00.662 --> 00:02:04.081
<i>The autobiography.
written by CEO Eli Hobson.</i>

42
00:02:04.082 --> 00:02:05.750
<i>describes how he saved Chrysler</i>

43
00:02:05.751 --> 00:02:08.210
<i>by leaning into
the boom in electric vehicles.</i>

44
00:02:12.633 --> 00:02:16.427
<i>The Y2K bug
is wreaking havoc in Earth orbit today</i>

45
00:02:16.428 --> 00:02:19.597
<i>after clocks aboard
the International Space Port reset to...</i>

46
00:02:19.598 --> 00:02:21.390
Fire!

47
00:02:21.391 --> 00:02:23.184
<i>The question on everyone's mind is.</i>

48
00:02:23.185 --> 00:02:26.604
<i>"Will Vice President Bush be able to
keep together the Wilson Coalition?"</i>

49
00:02:26.605 --> 00:02:28.689
<i>In a tightly contested election.</i>

50
00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:30.983
<i>Al Gore has defeated George Bush</i>

51
00:02:30.984 --> 00:02:33.903
<i>to become the 42nd president
of the United States.</i>

52
00:02:40.953 --> 00:02:42.912
<i>Chaos reigns in Riyadh tonight</i>

53
00:02:42.913 --> 00:02:46.874
<i>after insurgents seized key government
buildings in Saudi Arabia's capital.</i>

54
00:02:46.875 --> 00:02:49.544
The Osbournes
<i>and</i> Moon Miners <i>are leading the way</i>

55
00:02:49.545 --> 00:02:51.128
<i>for a new kind of television.</i>

56
00:02:51.129 --> 00:02:54.465
<i>It's being called reality TV.
and it's dominating the nightly ratings.</i>

57
00:02:54.466 --> 00:02:57.009
<i>Glasnost and perestroika has transformed</i>

58
00:02:57.010 --> 00:03:00.346
<i>the once dour Russian capital
into a city of light and even...</i>

59
00:03:05.352 --> 00:03:07.895
<i>The alliance
between Gore and the Soviet leader</i>

60
00:03:07.896 --> 00:03:09.564
<i>shows no sign of slowing down.</i>

61
00:03:09.565 --> 00:03:11.816
<i>As we usher in a new decade.</i>

62
00:03:11.817 --> 00:03:15.611
the growing partnership between
the United States and the Soviet Union.

63
00:03:15.612 --> 00:03:17.572
both on Earth and on Mars.

64
00:03:17.573 --> 00:03:21.617
is bringing a new sense of optimism
to the nations of the world.

65
00:03:21.618 --> 00:03:26.164
<i>Tonight. I can proudly say
that the Cold War is over.</i>

66
00:03:26.748 --> 00:03:31.002
<i>Those we once thought of as our enemies
have become our friends</i>

67
00:03:31.003 --> 00:03:35.047
<i>and a new era of peace
and prosperity is before us.</i>

68
